I'm writing a Go web service. I want to set up the database connection pool when the application starts. Here's my approach:

```go
var db *sql.DB

func init() {
    var err error
    db, err = sql.Open("postgres", os.Getenv("DATABASE_URL"))
    if err != nil {
        log.Fatal(err)
    }
}
```

Is this a good pattern? How should I improve it?
